HEADWORD: Demicadence
<hw>Dem"i*ca`dence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>
<def>An imperfect or half cadence, falling on the dominant instead of on
the key note.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

